Given the following program and the specified variable, optimize it out by constant propagation or copy propagation. If this variable is unused, just optimize it out.. The program is 
struct h {
  int i;
  long j;
  int k;
};

static struct h fn1(struct h p4) {
  while (1)
    p4 = p4;
}

int fn2() {
  struct h p;
  struct h r;
  fn1(p);
  while (1)
    p = r = p;
}

int main() {
  // No optimizations made
}
.                 The target to be optimized is `r` in `fn2()` is assigned but not used..
